Most of the extreme-thermophilic members of Phylum Clostridia utilize the “Embden-Meyerhof pathway” for H2 fermentation. In the first route, NADH, formed in the Embden-Meyerhof pathway, is utilized by NADH-dependent Fe-only H2ase to evolve H2 according to the following equation [44, 69]:11NADH+H+→NAD++H2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
